=You are an AI assistant for a freight brokerage customer support team.

Analyze the following email and classify it into exactly one of these three categories:
1. SHIPMENT_STATUS - Customer asking where their load is or requesting an ETA
2. RATE_QUOTE - Customer requesting a price quote for a shipment
3. POD_REQUEST - Customer requesting proof of delivery or signed BOL for a load

Email Subject: {{ $input.item.json.Subject }}
Email Body: {{ $input.item.json.snippet }}
Sender: {{ $input.item.json.From }}

Respond with ONLY a JSON object in this exact format, nothing else:
{
  "category": "SHIPMENT_STATUS",
  "load_number": "extracted load number or null",
  "origin": "extracted origin or null",
  "destination": "extracted destination or null",
  "sender_email": "sender email address"
}

=You are a professional customer support agent for a freight brokerage.

Based on the investigation results below, write a helpful and professional email response to the customer.

Category: {{ $input.item.json.category }}
Sender: {{ $input.item.json.sender_email }}
Load Number: {{ $input.item.json.load_number }}
Investigation Result: {{ JSON.stringify($input.item.json.investigation) }}

Write a short, professional email response that:
- Addresses the customer's request directly
- Includes all relevant information from the investigation
- Is friendly and concise
- Does not include a subject line
- Signs off as "Freight Support Team"

Return only the email body, nothing else.

parameters.jsCode:
// Grab Claude's raw text response from the previous node
const claudeOutput = $input.item.json.content[0].text;

// Parse the JSON from Claude's response
const jsonMatch = claudeOutput.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
const parsed = JSON.parse(jsonMatch[0]);

// Extract the two key fields Claude identified
const category = parsed.category;
const loadNumber = parsed.load_number;

// Mock TMS data — simulates a real TMS API response by load number
const mockTMS = {
  "1234592": {
    load_number: "1234592",
    status: "In Transit",
    origin: "Cincinnati, OH",
    destination: "Chicago, IL",
    driver: "Mike Johnson",
    carrier: "Swift Transportation",
    eta: "April 9, 2026 by 3:00 PM",
    last_location: "Indianapolis, IN as of 8:00 AM"
  },
  "45823": {
    load_number: "45823",
    status: "Delivered",
    origin: "Atlanta, GA",
    destination: "Chicago, IL",
    driver: "Sarah Williams",
    carrier: "Werner Enterprises",
    eta: "Delivered April 7, 2026 at 2:30 PM",
    last_location: "Chicago, IL"
  }
};

// Mock rate data — simulates a rate engine lookup by lane
const mockRates = {
  "Cincinnati-Chicago": { rate: "$850", transit_time: "1 day", carrier: "Swift Transportation" },
  "Atlanta-Chicago": { rate: "$1,200", transit_time: "2 days", carrier: "Werner Enterprises" },
  "default": { rate: "$950", transit_time: "2-3 days", carrier: "Best available carrier" }
};

// Mock POD data — simulates a document retrieval system by load number
const mockPODs = {
  "1234592": { pod_url: "https://tms.brokerage.com/pods/1234592.pdf", signed_by: "John Smith", delivery_time: "April 7, 2026 at 2:30 PM" },
  "45823": { pod_url: "https://tms.brokerage.com/pods/45823.pdf", signed_by: "Mary Johnson", delivery_time: "April 7, 2026 at 11:00 AM" }
};

let investigationResult = {};

// Route to the correct data source based on Claude's classification
if (category === "SHIPMENT_STATUS") {
  if (!loadNumber) {
    // No load number extracted — flag for human follow up
    investigationResult = { error: "No load number provided", message: "Please ask the customer to provide their load number so we can look up the shipment status." };
  } else {
    // Look up load in TMS — if not found, flag for manual lookup
    investigationResult = mockTMS[loadNumber] || { error: "Load not found", message: "No shipment found for load " + loadNumber + ". May need manual lookup." };
  }
} else if (category === "RATE_QUOTE") {
  // Build lane key from origin/destination and pull rate
  const key = `${parsed.origin}-${parsed.destination}`;
  investigationResult = mockRates[key] || mockRates["default"];
} else if (category === "POD_REQUEST") {
  if (!loadNumber) {
    // No load number extracted — flag for human follow up
    investigationResult = { error: "No load number provided", message: "Please ask the customer to provide their load number so we can look up the POD." };
  } else {
    // Look up POD document — if not found, flag for manual lookup
    investigationResult = mockPODs[loadNumber] || { error: "POD not found", message: "No POD found for load " + loadNumber + ". May need manual lookup." };
  }
}

// Default to Processed — switch to Needs Action if investigation failed
let labelId = "Label_7769852500067835149"; // Processed
if (investigationResult.error) {
  labelId = "Label_1580129994340978842"; // Needs Action
}

// Pass all data forward to the reply drafter and label nodes
return [
  {
    json: {
      category: category,
      load_number: loadNumber,
      sender_email: parsed.sender_email,
      origin: parsed.origin,
      destination: parsed.destination,
      investigation: investigationResult,
      labelId: labelId
    }
  }
];
